SETTING: An urban canal towpath. The path is tarmac or packed gravel. To one side: calm canal water reflecting morning light. To the other: a row of mature trees casting long early shadows across the path. A second jogger is visible 40–50 metres behind, out of focus. The towpath stretches back into soft depth of field.
CAMERA: Shot from slightly ahead and to the right, at path level, as if a running partner turned around mid-stride to photograph him. 35mm or 50mm equivalent. Shallow depth of field — subject sharp, background progressively blurred. Low morning sun from the left, casting long directional shadows. The watch face catches a small glint of sunlight.
