ser-message-bubble-color corner-superellipse/0.98 relative rounded-[22px] px-4 py-2.5 leading-6 max-w-(--user-chat-width,70%)"><div class="whitespace-pre-wrap">SUBJECT: A couple in their early-to-mid 30s in a vintage open-top car on a coastal road. The woman is driving — one hand on the wheel, the other resting on the gear stick, wearing large sunglasses and a light cotton shirt. The man is in the passenger seat, arm draped along the back of the seat, head turned toward the view, squinting slightly in the daylight. Both are clearly distinct from the car interior — visible separation between their bodies and the seats, door panels, and dashboard.
VEHICLE: A classic vintage car, cream or faded white bodywork, tan leather seats, minimal dashboard detail. Convertible, roof fully down. The car is mid-motion on the road — not static. Paintwork slightly imperfect — not showroom condition.
SETTING: A winding coastal road. The cliff drops to the ocean on one side. Rocky outcrops and dry scrub vegetation line the roadside. The road curves away in both directions with no other vehicles visible. Tarmac surface with natural wear — faded road markings, uneven edges.
LIGHT: Bright midday or early afternoon daylight. High sun, slightly harsh, casting short strong shadows inside the car and on the road surface. No golden tones — white Mediterranean-style light. Slight squint-inducing brightness. The kind of light that makes colours look slightly washed at the edges.
CAMERA: Shot from slightly above and behind the car, as if from a following vehicle at low altitude. The car fills the lower two-thirds of the frame. 1:1 square crop. 35mm equivalent. Shallow depth of field — the couple and car sharp, coastal landscape behind softening naturally.
STYLE: Photojournalistic documentary photography. Realistic skin, hair, and material textures — sweat, slight windblown hair, creased clothing. Fine natural film grain — not digital noise. Flat, true-to-life colour — no warm grade, no filters, no saturation boost. The image feels like it was taken without the subjects noticing. Imperfect framing, not composed for beauty. No AI smoothing, no plastic skin, no merging of figures with car interior or background.</div></div></div></div></div><div class="z-0 flex justify-end"><div aria-label="Your message actions" class="touch:-me-2 touch:-ms-3.5 -ms-2.5 -me-1 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-y-4 p-1 select-none focus-within:transition-none hover:transition-none touch:pointer-events-auto touch:opacity-100 duration-300 group-hover/turn-messages:delay-300 pointer-events-none opacity-0 motion-safe:transition-opacity group-hover/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-hover/turn-messages:opacity-100 group-focus-within/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-focus-within/turn-messages:opacity-100 has-data-[state=open]:pointer-events-auto has-data-[state=open]:opacity-100" role="group" tabindex="-1" style="mask-position: 0% 0%;"><button class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-bg-secondary rounded-lg" aria-label="Copy message" data-testid="copy-turn-action-button" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button><button class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-bg-secondary rounded-lg" aria-label="Edit message" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#6d87e1" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span>