-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none [--shadow-height:45px] has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none has-data-writing-block:-mt-(--shadow-height) has-data-writing-block:pt-(--shadow-height) [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto scroll-mt-(--header-height)" dir="auto" data-turn-id="65db3268-5084-42b6-b357-1485830d3279" data-testid="conversation-turn-17" data-scroll-anchor="false" data-turn="user"><h4 class="sr-only select-none">You said:</h4><div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto pt-12 [--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-xs,calc(var(--spacing)*4))] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-sm,calc(var(--spacing)*6))] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)" style="scroll-margin-top: -1044px;"><div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow"><div data-message-author-role="user" data-message-id="65db3268-5084-42b6-b357-1485830d3279" dir="auto" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden items-end rtl:items-start"><div class="user-message-bubble-color corner-superellipse/0.98 relative rounded-[22px] px-4 py-2.5 leading-6 max-w-(--user-chat-width,70%)"><div class="whitespace-pre-wrap">SUBJECT: A solo hiker — gender indeterminate from behind — standing at the rocky summit edge, back fully to the camera, hands on hips. Medium build, upright but relaxed posture, weight distributed evenly between both feet. Wearing a weathered waterproof jacket, waterproof trousers, well-worn hiking boots, and a plain knitted beanie. A large hiking backpack sits high on their back — hip belt fastened, a sleeping mat strapped horizontally to the bottom, one or two small items clipped to the outside. No reflective gear, no brand logos prominent. They are standing still — not moving, fully absorbed in the view. Clearly separated from the rocky ground beneath their boots.
SETTING: A mountain summit, rocky and exposed. Uneven ground — large flat stones, loose scree, patches of dark moss and grey-green lichen on the rocks. A cairn of hand-stacked stones is visible to one side, slightly out of focus — rough, irregular, built over time by many different hands. No trail markers, no signs, no infrastructure. The summit feels genuinely remote.
VIEW: The valley below is completely filled with cloud — a dense white layer like a still sea, flat-topped and unbroken except where two or three distant peaks protrude through it as dark shapes. No towns, no roads, no human detail visible in the valley. The cloud surface has subtle texture — not uniform white, slight variation in density.
LIGHT: Flat, diffused grey daylight — overcast, no direct sun. A faint, directionless glow through the cloud layer above, slightly brighter toward one side of the sky. The light is cold and even, casting almost no shadows. Visibility is clear at summit level but the mist at the valley edge drifts and shifts — thin wisps detaching and moving slowly upward at the cliff edge. No golden tones, no drama — honest mountain weather light.
CAMERA: Shot from a few metres behind and slightly to one side — as if taken by a fellow hiker seated on a rock, camera held at seated eye level. The hiker occupies the centre-left or centre-right of the frame, not dead centre. The cairn sits in the near background, slightly soft. 1:1 square crop. 35mm equivalent. Shallow depth of field — hiker and immediate foreground rocks sharp, valley cloud and distant peaks softening into the grey. Slightly unsteady framing — handheld, not tripod.
STYLE: Photojournalistic outdoor documentary photography. Realistic fabric, rock, moss, and mist textures — worn jacket material, scuffed boot leather, damp-looking stone surfaces. Fine natural film grain — not digital noise. Flat, desaturated true-to-life colour — cold grey-green palette, no warming filter, no contrast boost. The image feels like it was taken quickly and quietly by someone who didn't want to interrupt the moment. Imperfect framing, slightly asymmetric. No AI smoothing, no merging of figure with rocky ground or skyline. The hiker is fully distinct against the cloud-filled valley behind them.</div></div></div></div></div><div class="z-0 flex justify-end"><div aria-label="Your message actions" class="touch:-me-2 touch:-ms-3.5 -ms-2.5 -me-1 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-y-4 p-1 select-none focus-within:transition-none hover:transition-none touch:pointer-events-auto touch:opacity-100 duration-300 group-hover/turn-messages:delay-300 pointer-events-none opacity-0 motion-safe:transition-opacity group-hover/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-hover/turn-messages:opacity-100 group-focus-within/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-focus-within/turn-messages:opacity-100 has-data-[state=open]:pointer-events-auto has-data-[state=open]:opacity-100" role="group" tabindex="-1" style="mask-position: 0% 0%;"><button class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-bg-secondary rounded-lg" aria-label="Copy message" data-testid="copy-turn-action-button" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button><button class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-bg-secondary rounded-lg" aria-label="Edit message" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg